          "date": "2017-12-07 13:19:49.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-7058 utils: Allow lfs migrate to operate on directories",
        "message": "LU-7058 utils: Allow lfs migrate to operate on directories\n\nWhen directory names are provided to the lfs migrate command,\nthe contents of the directory are migrated instead of returning\n-EISDIR. A new sanity test verifies that directory contents are\nrecursively migrated.\n\nThe help text for the migrate command is cleaned up, and now uses\na macro for options that are common with the setstripe command.\n\nThe --component-end|-E and --layout|-L options were missing from\nthe lfs migrate man page, and have been added.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Steve Guminski <stephenx.guminski@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I5cf187ce8bd5b475a39201c44a3fd6f8b5b747f9\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
